        <p>Thomas Jefferson's attitude toward wine (''Jefferson Gets His Wish: At Last, a Decent Bottle of Virginia Wine,'' Sept. 13) is perhaps best summarized in a letter he wrote to a friend in 1818.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thomas Jefferson's attitude toward wine (''Jefferson Gets His Wish: At Last, a Decent Bottle of Virginia Wine,'' Sept. 13) is perhaps best summarized in a letter he wrote to a friend in 1818.</p>
        <p>No nation is drunken where wine is cheap; and none sober, where the dearness of wine substitutes ardent spirits as the common beverage.</p>
        <p>NIS PETERSEN  New York</p>
      </block>
